sentences.content: The reset button clears fill-in prompt fields and removes strikethroughs from the responses.
When no prompts or responses have been changed, the reset button is disabled.
The show tagging button displays tags for prompts and responses.
The hide tagging button hides tags for prompts and responses.
The tagging button is disabled when no tags are available in the section.
The show progression order button displays the slider that adjusts the order of responses and reveal of prompt fill-ins.
The slider allows the order change progressively from easy to difficult:
Fill-in field within each prompt is shown.
Fill-in field within each prompt is hidden while responses from the section are listed in order.
Fill-in field within each prompt is hidden while responses from the section are listed alphabetically.
Fill-in field within each prompt is hidden while responses from the section are listed randomly.
Fill-in field within each prompt is hidden while responses from the section are hidden.
The hide progression order button hides the slider.

heading.content: Arrange responses as grid or comma-separated values

sentences.content: The arrange responses layout button displays the possible responses to prompts in a grid format.
The arrange responses layout button displays the possible responses to prompts in a list of comma-separated values.
The group by tags button displays responses grouped by their respective tags.
The ungroup from tags button removes responses grouping by tags.
The group by tags button is disabled when tags are hidden and/or no tags are available in the section.
